A: The problem is that you are using the same iterator for all children in your loop. You should create a new iterator for each child.
Here is the corrected code:
names=new ArrayList<>();
rootRef.addValueEventListener(new ValueEventListener() {
    @Override
    public void onDataChange(DataSnapshot dataSnapshot) {
        for (DataSnapshot dataSnapshot1:dataSnapshot.getChildren()) {
            i = i + 1;
            names.add(dataSnapshot1.getValue(String.class));
        }
        Toast.makeText(signup.this,""+names,Toast.LENGTH_LONG).show();
    }

    @Override
    public void onCancelled(DatabaseError databaseError) {
        // Handle error
    }
});

In this code, dataSnapshot1 is the iterator for each child in the loop. So, dataSnapshot1.getValue(String.class) will give you the value of the current child.

